author: National Geographic
description:
Paid content for @Prada. Overfishing, pollution, and climate change are disrupting the world's great kelp forests. Prada Group and UNESCO-IOC have launched the SEA BEYOND educational program, inspiring a new wave of action to understand and preserve our ocean. Join actress Sadie Sink and SEA BEYOND Goodwill Ambassador Giovanni Chimienti as they explore the Kelp Forest Highway—revealing how both humans and marine life rely on its resources and what we can do to restore this forgotten forest.
